<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-02T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-02T01:00:00-05:00" n="527" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50/11–244: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-02T09:00:00+03:00">November 2,
                                1944—9 a.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received 12:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>4194. ReEmbs 4001, October 20, 1 p.m. The British Ambassador has received a
                        letter from Vyshinski dated October 28 stating that the British proposal for
                        the establishment of an European Economic Committee had been referred to the
                        appropriate Soviet authorities <pb facs="0640" n="630" xml:id="pg_630"/> for
                        study and requesting further information concerning the proposed tasks,
                        functions and structure of the committee.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>